gate: LOCKED
sprint: S04
track: B
task: B3
title: "bug: AbortSignal.timeout on fetch-inventory admin endpoint (#1255)"
repos: [crop-front]
priority: P2
refs:
  - CROP-front#1255
requires: [NEXTJS_VERCEL_FRONTEND, TYPESCRIPT]

description: |
  The staff fetch-inventory admin endpoint has no per-request timeout — a slow
  or hung upstream response holds the server action indefinitely. Same pattern
  as UPS timeout fixes in S04 Track A (crop-parts-services). Fix: add
  AbortSignal.timeout() to the fetch call with a sensible ceiling (suggest 10s
  for admin endpoints).

scope:
  in:
    - Locate fetch-inventory fetch call in staff/admin route or server action
    - Add AbortSignal.timeout(10_000) to the fetch options
    - Unit test: mock fetch hangs → expect abort within ceiling
  out:
    - Changing the inventory API contract or response shape
    - Other admin endpoints (separate issues)

acceptance:
  - fetch-inventory aborts at ≤ 10s ceiling
  - AbortError surfaces as a user-visible error message (not a silent hang)
  - Unit test confirms abort behavior

dep: none
output: fetch-inventory call site patched + unit test
